<a name="1">&nbsp;</a>
<div class="sponsorshipTitle">Paperless Press Kit Distribution in Press Room:&nbsp;<span class="lt_blue">FREE</span></div>
<br />
<p style="text-align: left; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); ">
	The International CES is one of the largest media events of the year, and your press kit is your most valuable media tool at CES. This year the CES press kit area is once again going green!<br />
	<br />
	In an effort to reduce our environmental footprint and in accordance with media feedback, both the LVCC and The Venetian press rooms will ONLY house paperless exhibitor press kits. Exhibitors are encouraged to use our Online Media Center, hosted by BusinessWire, or bring in press kits loaded to USB or CD. Your kit may be accompanied by one sheet of printed material that lists media contacts and/or the URL that your online press kit is housed at.. Printed press materials greater than one page in length should be stored in the exhibitor&rsquo;s booth. Make sure your press kit area is marked clearly with your company&#39;s name and CES booth number for easy reference.<br />
	<br />
	Press kits are a one-stop source for the media to get information about your company and products. Information included in kits should be kept simple and to the point&mdash;journalists are after hard news. Make sure your kits are in the Press Room, to gain valuable exposure to an influential audience! Prepare at least 250-500 electronic kits for distribution or host online.<br />
	<br />
	Traditional paper press kits will NOT be accepted.<br />
	<br />
	Paperless Press Kits marked to arrive December 30, 2012 through January 3, 2013</p>
